01:03:36.920 --> 01:03:39.640
They didn't know we
were still writing.

01:03:39.640 --> 01:03:44.420
And so, when we got
involved in this whole thing,

01:03:44.420 --> 01:03:49.650
all of a sudden there
was this opportunity

01:03:49.650 --> 01:03:53.010
with these huge crowds
of people coming --

01:03:53.010 --> 01:03:54.830
thousands of people came
to listen [inaudible].

01:03:54.830 --> 01:04:02.280
They stayed a whole week in
Elko and would go from sessions

01:04:02.280 --> 01:04:09.810
to session to session
and spend money

01:04:09.810 --> 01:04:12.860
on the night shows
to hear this stuff.

01:04:12.860 --> 01:04:16.520
And we're sitting
there thinking,

01:04:16.520 --> 01:04:18.150
we wrote this [inaudible].

01:04:18.150 --> 01:04:27.310
So, when I first got <i>The Body
Burning Detail </i>from Bill Jones

01:04:27.310 --> 01:04:30.790
and later got [inaudible]
from Rod McQueary we thought,

01:04:30.790 --> 01:04:35.910
there's all these people here,

01:04:35.910 --> 01:04:45.190
why not add these
other poems in.

01:04:45.190 --> 01:04:46.490
And it worked.

01:04:46.490 --> 01:04:52.120
So, I would say that
there's got to be a way

01:04:52.120 --> 01:04:54.050
to get people to come listen.

01:04:54.050 --> 01:05:00.670
[Inaudible].

01:05:00.670 --> 01:05:02.000
That's what I would say.

01:05:02.000 --> 01:05:04.490
Figure out a way and
make it -- make it fun.

01:05:04.490 --> 01:05:05.790
[Inaudible].

01:05:05.790 --> 01:05:22.260
But in the writing that we
do, [inaudible] message at war

01:05:22.260 --> 01:05:24.890
with one another [inaudible].

01:05:24.890 --> 01:05:27.100
That's not us.

01:05:27.100 --> 01:05:32.460
It starts with a story
and ends [inaudible].

01:05:32.460 --> 01:05:33.970
